headline: FDSE at Palantir Technologies
about: I feel best when I am actively engaged as part of a team working towards a meaningful goal. I love working on the tough parts of projects that can easily slide under the radar: the details. I’m obsessed with clean code, collaborative teams, and empowered customers.

experience.location: New York, New York, United States
experience.description:
Palantir is a technology company focused on empowering domain experts to leverage their expertise against high scale data assets.
My role is as a Forward Deployed Software Engineer. As such, I have two complimentary responsibilities:
1. Embed with client teams developing solutions on Palantir' platform products to build efficient, maintainable, and business impacting data processes and user applications built on Palantir's platforms.
2. Derive insights into the cutting edge of the product's capabilities as our most advanced users bump up against them, bring those back to the product group and peers across other forward deployments to arbitrate on solution design and eventually incorporate the appropriate feature additions into our product suite.

OpenJAUS is a robotics company. The flagship product is the OpenJAUS SDK which is a C++ implementation of the SAE JAUS standard, enabling customers to create and use JAUS enabled hardware with ease. While here, I've made large improvements to the SDK, decreasing build times as well as improving error reporting and log messages, and I spearheaded an effort to knock out almost all of our technical debt. I've also built a few on-demand applications to deliver solutions to clients, and I continue to work with the team to improve the SDK.

Wonderment Apps is a software design and development consultancy based in Los Angeles. I signed on as a temporary contractor in the role of Technical Project Owner. I launched a project to create internal process documentation and streamline and improve existing processes. I also managed several client accounts, followed up daily with internal workers and project stakeholders, managed the project budgets and projected spending, and handled situations with difficult stakeholders.

Celo is a start-up out of San Francisco working on a mobile-based stable crypto currency for the developing world. My job was to develop a stable SMS-based new user verification system. I used a combination of Google Cloud Services, Firebase, Typescript, and React Native. I also was a flex engineer working to support a variety of other teams including our mobile development team, dev ops, and contracts team.

I began working for Microsoft when they acquired Intentional Software. They hired me to continue the work I had been doing on the Intentional applications platform.

-- Developed, pitched, and managed two summer intern projects, adding new features to  text-layout system
-- Partnered with teams within Microsoft to optimize and unify our Text-Layout story across the company
-- Responded to urgent need on the Accessibility team for extra help, quickly transitioned to full-time work on creating and providing the necessary platform features to push our flagship application into compliance

-- Implemented extensive refactor to our Text-Layout back-end, making it cross-platform compatible
-- Designed and implemented a self-contained Text-Layout testing module, enabling us to decrease the degree of integration for our tests and find the sources of bugs faster
-- Designed, implemented and tested our entire Text-Layout back-end module for iOS and Mac systems

-- Compiled, updated, and maintained distribution lists, newsletters, and web pages.
-- Produced marketing content in the form of written copy, graphics for event advertisements, and video for social media using WordPress CMS, Adobe Photoshop, and Adobe Premiere.

Supervisor: Brenda Ellis
20 hours/week
Built an internal development tool on the Intentional Platform that provides a direct view and editing interface for underlying data structures and program state of Intentional Applications.

projects.title: Sophomore Design Project
projects.description: Worked with a partner to program a robot to follow a black line across a maze. The robot was programmed using C. NMCT by HOWEST, University College West Flanders, is a young professional bachelor that educates students to all round IT professionals with the newest tools, technologies, languages and frameworks.
A very broad amount of topics from computer networking to visual design are covered over three years. As you advance through the bachelor you can focus more on your area of interest within the world of IT.
I specialized in development for the web, desktop and mobile.
The bachelor contains multiple big projects where the students improve the learned project management and technical skills .
education.insights:
Grade: Greatest Honor
Activities and societies: Web, desktop & mobile development, programming, designing, data communication, computer networking, etc.

education.schoolName: The Washington Center for Internships and Academic Seminars
education.description:
The Washington Center provides housing and an internship in Washinton D.C. to promising students from all over the world. Academic seminars are given outside the internship to improve career skills and leadership skills.
With the civic engagement program students also contribute to society.
education.insights: Activities and societies: Internship, professional development, culture, politics, speaking, leadership, career, networking and media & communication.
